# 0. Golden Rule

Every development decision must follow these principles:

- Simpler is better.
- Maintainability is more important than cleverness.
- Conversion is more important than technology.
- Build for the next real customer, not for imaginary future requirements.
- Never over-engineer.

Our goal is **not to build an e-commerce platform.**

Our goal is to build **a sales machine**.

---

# 1. Project Philosophy

This project is NOT:

- Shopify Clone
- Amazon Clone
- Full Shopping Mall
- Enterprise Management System

This project IS:

A lightweight DTC website focused on product conversion.

Core business flow:

TikTok
↓

Landing Page
↓

PayPal Checkout
↓

Successful Payment

↓

Customer Confirmation

Every feature must improve at least one of:

- Trust
- Conversion
- User Experience
- Performance

Otherwise, do not build it.

---

# 2. Development Philosophy

Business first.

Technology second.

Every new feature should answer:

"Will this increase conversions?"

If not, postpone it.

Do not build features simply because they are technically interesting.

---

# 3. Technical Stack

Frontend

- Next.js (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS

Deployment

- GitHub
- Vercel

Payment

- PayPal Checkout

Future

- Supabase (Database)
- Stripe (Optional)

No unnecessary technologies.

Avoid introducing additional frameworks unless absolutely necessary.

---

# 4. Project Structure

Standard directory structure:

app/

components/

components/ui/

components/layout/

components/product/

lib/

hooks/

styles/

public/

content/

types/

Do not create random folders.

Maintain consistency.

---

# 5. Component Design Rules

Each component has ONE responsibility.

Good examples:

Hero.tsx

FeatureGrid.tsx

ReviewSection.tsx

FAQ.tsx

CheckoutButton.tsx

Footer.tsx

Bad example:

LandingPage.tsx (3000+ lines)

Components should be:

- Reusable
- Independent
- Easy to maintain

---

# 6. UI Design Principles

Visual style:

Apple

Tesla

Notion

Raycast

Linear

Keywords:

Minimal

Premium

Elegant

Calm

Clean

Timeless

Avoid:

Over decoration

Crypto style

Cyberpunk

Heavy gradients

Large glowing effects

Colorful interfaces

Visual consistency is more important than creativity.

---

# 7. Performance First

Performance has higher priority than animation.

Prefer:

Static Rendering

Server Components

Image Optimization

Lazy Loading

Minimal JavaScript

Avoid unnecessary client-side rendering.

---

# 8. Cursor Collaboration Rules

Cursor is our engineering assistant.

Cursor should NEVER:

- Rewrite the whole project.
- Refactor unrelated files.
- Introduce unnecessary dependencies.
- Modify project architecture without explanation.

Cursor SHOULD:

- Solve one task at a time.
- Explain why changes are needed.
- Keep existing structure.
- Reuse existing components.

Development principle:

Small changes.

Frequent testing.

Incremental progress.

---

# 9. Git Rules

Commit messages:

feat:

fix:

style:

docs:

refactor:

Avoid:

update

modify

change

Always write meaningful commit messages.

---

