## Documentation Principles

Documentation should remain stable over time.

Avoid framework versions, package versions, and implementation-specific details in specification documents.

Specifications define principles, responsibilities, and architecture boundaries.

Technology versions and implementation details belong in reference documents.

If documentation conflicts with assumptions, always follow the documentation.